Step-by-Step to Audit Working vault-0 Setup in Namespace xyz
1Ô∏è‚É£ Get All Resources in xyz Namespace
bash
Copy
Edit
oc get all -n xyz
2Ô∏è‚É£ Describe the vault StatefulSet
bash
Copy
Edit
oc describe statefulset vault -n xyz
3Ô∏è‚É£ Export the StatefulSet YAML
bash
Copy
Edit
oc get statefulset vault -n xyz -o yaml > vault-statefulset.yaml
4Ô∏è‚É£ Get PVCs Used by Vault
bash
Copy
Edit
oc get pvc -n xyz
Then describe the one used by vault-0 (e.g., vault-storage):

bash
Copy
Edit
oc describe pvc vault-storage -n xyz
5Ô∏è‚É£ Identify PersistentVolume Linked to PVC
bash
Copy
Edit
oc get pv | grep vault-storage
Then describe it:

bash
Copy
Edit
oc describe pv <pv-name>
6Ô∏è‚É£ Get All StorageClasses (Find the One Used by Vault)
bash
Copy
Edit
oc get storageclass
oc describe storageclass <rook-ceph-sc-name>
Look for:

provisioner: rook-ceph.rbd.csi.ceph.com

volumeBindingMode: Immediate

7Ô∏è‚É£ List All Rook-Ceph Pods
bash
Copy
Edit
oc get pods -n rook-ceph
8Ô∏è‚É£ Get Rook-Ceph Operator Logs
bash
Copy
Edit
oc logs -n rook-ceph deploy/rook-ceph-operator
9Ô∏è‚É£ Export the StorageClass YAML Used by Vault
bash
Copy
Edit
oc get storageclass <rook-sc-name> -o yaml > rook-sc.yaml
üîü Get Vault Image Used
bash
Copy
Edit
oc get pod vault-0 -n xyz -o jsonpath='{.spec.containers[0].image}'
üßæ Bonus: Export All YAMLs from Working Namespace
bash
Copy
Edit
oc get all -n xyz -o yaml > xyz-all.yaml
And rook-ceph (if you want full backup):

bash
Copy
Edit
oc get all -n rook-ceph -o yaml > rook-all.yaml
